annotation.TEXT: DOUBLE KILL!
Whoops, I don't want to discard both.
Alright, that unlocked 2-6, but there's gotta be a secret exit in this place, since the other levels next to that shop didn't have secret exits. And, I still need the moon, of course.
Whoa, geez, that scared me. I just barely cleared them. It didn't help that when I use Air Bound, I lose my horizontal control for a split-second.
I think I know what I need to do to get the moon now, and that requires getting back up the way I came with Wind + Air Bound. Anyway, I get an achievement here.
Also, I'll get rid of these two guys just because they looked at me funny.
Oh, yeah! I definitely couldn't have done that without both Wind and Air Bound! I'm glad I didn't take the plunge without Wind the first time! But, can I get to safety now?
Also, there's the Wind magic, which I'll certainly buy. And, I guess I'll take 3 Jellied Yams too, just to contribute towards the 100 I need for the achievement.
No sense in worrying about saving those hearts, since I assume the red spikes are instant death anyway.
Okay, the red spikes only stretch 2 tiles away from the wall, so with a properly timed Air Bound...
Umm... Those coins are beckoning me... Uhh... Err...
Nice! However, it's not over yet. I have to do it again. Oh, but can I even get into the opening leading back up here?
You know what? I'd rather have Ground Spark than Ice.
Okay, beckoning coins, I'm finally coming for you. (Man, this is scary again. If I blow it here, I'll have to start the level over and redo that red spike zone.)
Ha! I knew you'd try to pull a fast one on me there, game! Oh, hey, a shop.
First, get Air Bound again, and I'm just gonna head straight for the red spike zone this time. I'm not gonna worry about clearing out all of the nearby enemies first.
Oh, what? The game let me land on that moon block from a ledge 7 tiles below with Wind alone. Huh, I guess it's a bit finicky with whether it lets me go 7 tiles high or not.
YES!!! Wow, I'm sooo thankful I didn't screw that up! Okay, let's get to the goal now.
I really like Ground Spark. It's got good range and can hit enemies in some unusual places.
Oh. God. No.
Alright, fingers, don't fail me now!
D'oh! Those bouncing balls are hard to predict. Sometimes they turn around when they hit a ceiling, and sometimes they don't.
Okay, I'm gonna clear out this guy now so he doesn't bother me, and with Ground Spark, I can take out the enemy that I know is down below.
BTW, who sets up a shop in such a dangerous area anyway? (Well, that could be asked of certain shops in many games.)
Of course, I'll still whack that guy, just in case.
I'll take your Fire, thank you very much.
Also, why is Fire even available in this shop down here? It's totally useless at this location.
Nuts, missed the top coin.
Okay, the ground doesn't continue very far past the goal. Umm... What to do?
I doubt there's anything further to the right... Oh, but what's this?
Yeah, I was expecting this familiar music to play here.
Hello, and welcome back to Tobari! Last time, I finished 2-4 and ended on this "Empty" level dot. Now, let's see what 2-5 is about...
Now, I certainly don't need two Air Bound spells. (I wonder if there'll ever be a point where you'd want to be holding two copies of the same spell...)
Ohhh, my god! Yes, I made it out alive! Wow, that was so scary! Okay, now before I go for the moon, I wanna try for the two 1-ups up above again with this combo.
Whoa. That's gonna scare me every time. Also, I didn't even have to worry about that Thunder user, since I stomped him upon entry.
ERGH!!! ...Not quite. I think maybe if I had stomped that bird while it was further to the right... Anyway, I'll just grab Ground Spark from this duder now.
Okay, I've decided what I'll do. I'll just clear the level normally now, and then try investigating that red spike area early in the level. Maybe I'll find a Broom spell there.
Okay, now for the really scary part... I've gotta jump with Wind, then switch and quickly use Air Bound in midair. I'll make a couple of quick practice jumps down here first.
And of course I mean the normal goal, because I'd be insane to try for the secret goal now!
DOUBLE KILL!
Okay, that wasn't so bad with Air Bound.
Okay, this just takes me back to familiar territory.
Well, that was pretty neat how they lined up for me to do that.
Huh, that's odd. Usually Jellied Yam is only available right before a boss.
That hit didn't matter, due to the heart right there.
Maybe from the left side...
Getting only 10 coins? That's slightly disappointing, but not scary at all.
DOUBLE KILL!
Ha! Got the top coin there this time! So, everyone's OCD can rest easy now.
Pfft... Of course I miss every ledge and land on spikes. At least they weren't red spikes.
Pfft... Good thing I saved this heart.
Okay, I've decided I'll approach it from the left, because of the coins I saw that were beckoning me over there before.
Found the moon! ...Oh, but... I don't think I can reach it from here, even with Air Bound.
As for the others, I don't think I'll need Fire (but I'll come back if I do), and I can't buy Plum Tea while at full health.
And, I've now unlocked this world's Leisure Shop. I'll take a peek at it later. Right now, I need to focus on the moon.
Sweet! Got these two 1-ups!
Oh, there's the secret exit. But, is there anything beyond it? Well, with Wind + Air Bound, I think I can jump over it...
Whoa, very close call there!
Alright, time to head for the moon! It's about 238,855 miles (384,400 km) away on average, so this trip will take a while.
Ooh, 3 lives ain't bad.
Okay, so apparently, Wind alone can get me onto a 6-tile high ledge, but not 7. Air Bound alone can get me onto 7. And, combining them can get me onto 9.
DOUBLE KILL!
Alright, let's do this!
Oh, this is the other side of that double wall I approached from the right earlier. But, there's no way back... up... from... here...
Darn, I can't "ERGH!!!" enough to reach that coin. Welp, everyone's OCD is gonna go nuts for a while now.
Falling rocks? Not scary either.
Well, it appears to be the same as world 1's Leisure Shop. So, next time, world 2-6!
There's a lot of Air Bound magicians in this level. I guess the game really wants me to have Air Bound for navigating this place.
ERGH!!!
Oh, and with this combo, I have no means to attack besides stomping duders. So, the extra hearts from the Jellied Yams might come in handy on my way to the moon.
Ooh, I'll take that easy 1-up.
I'm guessing it'll be a cavern that's naturally huge.
Well, there's the goal, but there's an obvious path to the right of it. However, I can't see if there's actually land down there to the right of the goal...
Hey there, spikes below the ladder that could catch an unsuspecting person by surprise. How's it going?
In fact, I wonder if there are any hidden blocks in this game at all, like Amapani has... Anyway, anything to the left of this ledge? ...Geronimo!!!
Hmm... I'm curious what's down this hole. Well, I'll try to take a peek using Air Bound before I commit to falling down it...
Ooh, more coins.
DOUBLE KILL!
Well, unless Wind is available somewhere, it certainly looks like I'll need Air Bound to go places here.
Maybe I can see better from just to the left of the goal.
Moon count: 10
Also, I suspect there's something to the left of these walls here.
There's a rock thrower. Hmm... Maybe I should've tried using Shoot Rock here just for variety. Oh, well.
Whoa, dude. I still don't understand why you don't get Electro Spark from whacking that enemy. I wonder if that's an oversight by the developer.
COINS!!! Huh, that gap in the coins made me wonder if there were hidden blocks there.
MEGA KILL!
Okay, so there's an Air Bound duder. Is the game finally gonna force me to use Air Bound without having the Wind option available?
Okay, so first, get Air Bound. (And somehow strike a block that I'm standing on.)
Oh. God. No.
Edge of the level over here, so I guess I'm going down.
Okay, purchase Wind and 3 more Jellied Yams here.
Whoa! I saw that! There were red spikes down there! Good thing I peeked like that!
To be continued... Yo!
Aw, nuts. That would've been awesome if I had reached those two 1-ups. Also, apparently, I can reuse Air Bound again in the air if enough time passes.
Ow. Okay, ducking in the corner doesn't keep me completely safe from those bouncing balls.
That magician uses Thunder. Also, I saw an Ice magician to the right a moment ago. I have no idea what spells I'll eventually want to have down the road, though...
Okay, let's avoid these spikes, keeping in mind that touching the sides of them hurts, unlike in Amapani.
I'm trying to carefully avoid picking up that heart, in case I need it later.
Alright, here we go! GERONIMO!!!
Okay, so that clarifies something for me. If I'm carrying two medals and grab a third, the medal I'm holding but not currently equipped with is the one that vanishes.
Also, the moon is apparently moving away from Earth at a rate of about 1.5 inches (4 cm) per year, so I'd better not waste too much time getting there!
Wow, I am just playing stupidly now. I mean, seriously. I just jumped into that blatantly obvious spike ball that that guy had tossed.
I guess I'll try Ice for a while. Oh, whoops, I still want to hold onto Air Bound for now.
Gray spikes? Ha, you're not so scary.
Pfft... Failed to dodge that heart. Okay, now I don't think I fully explored what's to the right, so I'm going to take a quick peek before continuing to the left.
Okay, now how do I best approach the moon? Should I try from the right? Or from the left, starting from above the goal?
Next, I want to climb up here and try for the two 1-ups in the sky again. Also, I want to grab Ground Spark, which I think I remember being up there as well.
Oh, good. I need a heart. Oh, but I don't need an arrow in my face, so I'd better quickly fry that archer.
Huh, Wind alone isn't quite enough to get me onto that ledge.
Whoa, dude. Don't bother me while I'm pondering this situation here.
Alright, so 2-5 is completely done! And, I won't cliffhang you guys on the Leisure Shop this time.
I like that there's no "ascending glitch" in this game. Why is that even a thing in Mario games anyway?
